node.text: Two posts in one day cause it’s an important one. Happy #nationalaviationday ✈️ it’s insane what this industry has done for me and I couldn’t be more blessed. It’s truly changed my life simply from the pure enjoyment of aviation. Nothing in this world makes me happier than the messages I get from each of you on a daily basis telling me you found your passion for aviation through some piece of content I’ve made. It’s truly what I do it for. Thank you to every single one of you that’s given me this platform to help others 🖤 you have no idea what it means to me.

node.text: Damn this is gonna be a long one but hear me out. Social media can be so mentally draining. I started posting on this account five years ago. Before this account I had a personal one from all my high school friends and people I knew prior. On that account I would post whatever I want just like how most of you do. But as this account started to grow five years ago I started to put posting as a priority over so many other things in my life. I remember specifically one of my relationships in college I had to get up and get content, edit and post all before 9am everyday because I knew that’s what was best for the algorithm. I literally started prioritizing social media over relationships. Doesn’t that sound insane? It’s because it is but when you’re in the middle of it, it’s so hard to take a step back and realize that. This Instagram page specifically has given me so damn much that I’m thankful for. I’ve built brands, gone on dream vacations, purchased dream cars, and so on but NOTHING is more important then the people in your life. I felt like there was always something I needed to be doing at all hours of the day, and if I wasn’t doing some thing productive I would get down on myself and indirectly that would affect relationships. Over the last three months after getting out of my last relationship, I have been putting extreme focus on myself. I turn my “business” brain off at night now and relax. Some thing for the last five years I didn’t think was possible. So what’s the point of this whole post in general? One, if you’re in this space please remember to take time for yourself. Don’t allow other peoples opinions of being an “influencer” dictate how you spent your time. And two, I’m going to start focusing HEAVILY on posting what makes ME happy. Sure maybe I’ll lose followers but one thing I’ve definitely learned over the past 3-4 months is that mental health is way more valuable than likes, followers, and even money. So what does posting what makes me happy look like? Airline content and A LOT of it. Fitness because it’s a huge part of my life. And last but not least travel. So here’s to a 4 margarita deep, dirty elevator picture. Why?cause I want to. Love u🖤
